## 🛠️ Available Make Commands

```bash
make up              # Start all services
make down            # Stop all services
make logs            # View logs
make build           # Build the Go binary
make test            # Run tests
make fmt             # Format code
make lint            # Run golangci-lint
make clean           # Clean up
make swagger         # Generate Swagger docs
make migrate-up      # Run all pending migrations
make migrate-down    # Revert last migration
make migrate-create  # Create migration (NAME=migration_name)
make migrate-version # Show current migration version
make migrate-force   # Force migration version (VERSION=1)
```

## 📝 Adding New Endpoints

1. Create handler in `internal/handler/`
2. Add Swagger annotations to your handler function
3. Register route in `internal/server/server.go`
4. Run `make swagger` to regenerate docs
5. Add tests
6. Document in this README

**Example with Swagger annotations:**
```go
// GetUser godoc
// @Summary      Get user by ID
// @Description  Retrieve user details
// @Tags         users
// @Accept       json
// @Produce      json
// @Param        id   path      int  true  "User ID"
// @Success      200  {object}  map[string]interface{}
// @Router       /api/v1/users/{id} [get]
{{if eq .ServerType "gin"}}func (h *Handler) GetUser(c *gin.Context) {
	// Implementation
}{{else}}func (h *Handler) GetUser(c *fiber.Ctx) error {
	// Implementation
	return nil
}{{end}}
```

## 🗄️ Database Migrations

### Create a new migration
```bash
make migrate-create NAME=add_users_table
# Creates migrations/TIMESTAMP_add_users_table.up.sql
#     and migrations/TIMESTAMP_add_users_table.down.sql
```

### Run migrations
```bash
make migrate-up      # Apply all pending migrations
make migrate-version # Check current version
make migrate-down    # Rollback last migration
```

### Migration commands
```bash
# Via Makefile
make migrate-up
make migrate-down
make migrate-version

# Or directly
go run cmd/api/main.go migrate up
go run cmd/api/main.go migrate down
go run cmd/api/main.go migrate version
go run cmd/api/main.go migrate force 1
```

## 🐛 Troubleshooting

**Port already in use:**
```bash
# Change APP_PORT in .env
APP_PORT=8081
```

**Database connection failed:**
```bash
# Ensure Docker services are running
make up
```

**Redis connection failed:**
```bash
# Check Redis logs
docker compose logs redis
```

